{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Sr1mDihDqJNjKjzvV5cVZQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are clean and focused. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **`api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`** — Added `limit` field (field 5) to `StreamLogsRequest` for documentation.\n\n2. **`cmd/cloche/main.go`** — \n   - Added `-s` as short form for `--step`\n   - Added `-l` / `--limit <n>` flag that takes a positive integer\n   - Passes limit to the server via gRPC metadata header `x-cloche-limit`\n\n3. **`cmd/cloche/help.go`** — Updated help text to document `-s`, `-l` flags and combinability.\n\n4. **`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** — \n   - Added `limitFromContext()` to read limit from gRPC metadata\n   - Added `applyLimit()` helper that returns the last N lines of content\n   - Applied limit to: full.log output, capture-based step output, filtered logs, and follow mode initial snapshot\n   - Live-streamed lines in follow mode are not limited (matching `tail -f` behavior)\n\n5. **`internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go`** — Added 5 tests:\n   - `TestServer_StreamLogs_LimitFullLog` — limit truncates full.log to last N lines\n   - `TestServer_StreamLogs_LimitStepFilter` — limit applies to step-filtered output\n   - `TestServer_StreamLogs_LimitZeroReturnsAll` — no limit returns all content\n   - `TestServer_StreamLogs_LimitWithFollow` — limit truncates initial snapshot but streams all live lines\n   - `TestServer_StreamLogs_LimitCaptureOutput` — limit applies to capture-based per-step output\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":262,"cache_read_input_tokens":65558,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":262},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id